<i>noun</i>: 참작 [참작], 에누리 [에누리], 심의 [시ː믜/시ː미], 숙고 [숙꼬], 사료 [사료], 사려 [사려], 사념 [사념], 배려 [배ː려], 고찰 [고찰], 고심 [고심], 고려 [고려], 감안 [가만], 간주 [간주] <br>
<ul style="list-style-type:square">
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt>참작 [참작]</dt><br>
<dd>consideration; deliberation</dd><br>
<dd>결정하거나 판단할 때 어떤 일이나 상황을 참고하여 이리저리 헤아림.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of taking into account and thinking about something in making a decision or judgment.</dd><br>
<dt>에누리 [에누리]</dt><br>
<dd>1. overcharge</dd><br>
<dd>물건값을 받을 값보다 더 많이 부르는 일. 또는 그 물건값.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of demanding more money than the original price of something; a price that is higher than the original price.</dd><br>
<dd>2. discount</dd><br>
<dd>값을 깎는 일.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of reducing the price of something.</dd><br>
<dd>3. exaggeration; understatement</dd><br>
<dd>실제보다 더 보태거나 깎아서 말하는 일.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of overstating or understating something.</dd><br>
<dd>4. consideration</dd><br>
<dd>용서하거나 사정을 이해하고 봐주는 일.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of forgiving someone or understanding and considering someone's situation.</dd><br>
<dt>심의 [시ː믜/시ː미]</dt><br>
<dd>deliberation; consideration; review</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 내용이나 문제 등의 좋고 나쁨이나 알맞은 정도를 자세히 살핌.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of taking a good look at the quality or feasibility of a certain content, problem, etc.</dd><br>
<dt>숙고 [숙꼬]</dt><br>
<dd>deliberation; contemplation; consideration</dd><br>
<dd>깊고 신중히 잘 생각함. 또는 그런 생각.</dd><br>
<dd>The state of thinking about something deeply and carefully, or such a thought.</dd><br>
<dt>사료 [사료]</dt><br>
<dd>consideration; thinking; deliberation</dd><br>
<dd>깊이 생각하여 헤아림.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of thinking deeply to understand something.</dd><br>
<dt>사려 [사려]</dt><br>
<dd>1. thoughtfulness; consideration</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 일에 대하여 깊고 조심스럽게 생각함. 또는 그런 생각.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of thinking deeply and carefully about something, or such a thought.</dd><br>
<dd>2. thought; consideration; worries</dd><br>
<dd>걱정하고 애를 태우는 등의 여러 가지 생각.</dd><br>
<dd>An array of thoughts including worry, anxiety, etc.</dd><br>
<dt>사념 [사념]</dt><br>
<dd>thought; consideration; worries</dd><br>
<dd>마음 속으로 하는 여러 가지 생각.</dd><br>
<dd>An array of thoughts that one comes across.</dd><br>
<dt>배려 [배ː려]</dt><br>
<dd>consideration; thoughtfulness</dd><br>
<dd>관심을 가지고 보살펴 주거나 도와줌.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of being considerate about someone, caring for or helping him/her.</dd><br>
<dt>고찰 [고찰]</dt><br>
<dd>consideration; study</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 것을 깊이 생각하고 면밀히 연구함.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of studying and thinking about something deeply and closely.</dd><br>
<dt>고심 [고심]</dt><br>
<dd>consideration; contemplation; deliberation</dd><br>
<dd>해결하기 어려운 일에 대해 마음을 써 생각함.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of deliberating about a hard-to-solve problem.</dd><br>
<dt>고려 [고려]</dt><br>
<dd>consideration</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 일을 하는 데 여러 가지 상황이나 조건을 신중하게 생각함.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of giving careful thought to multiple situations or conditions in doing something.</dd><br>
<dt>감안 [가만]</dt><br>
<dd>allowance; consideration</dd><br>
<dd>여러 사정을 살펴서 생각함.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of thinking while considering a variety of different factors.</dd><br>
<dt>간주 [간주]</dt><br>
<dd>regard; consideration; count</dd><br>
<dd>무엇이 어떠하다고 생각되거나 여겨짐.</dd><br>
<dd>The state of something being thought or considered to have a certain trait.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>